com.github.stefanbirkner.editors

Class PropertyEditorWithMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.stefanbirkner.editors.PropertyEditorWithMapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PropertyEditor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EmptyStringToNullEditor

    public class PropertyEditorWithMapper
extends Object
implements PropertyEditor
    An PropertyEditorWithMapper modifies the text input and output of another PropertyEditor. A configurable mapper is used for the mapping. When somebody calls setAsText(...) on the new editor, then it uses the mapper to modify the text before it is supplied to the original PropertyEditor. The same happens when somebody calls getAsText().
    Since:
    2.0.0
    Author:
    Stefan Birkner
